snippet.textDisplay: Nice dress, not really, what's in it, Scarlett Johansson, not so much. Hollywood has always been infected with that cancer of the ego called narcissism, but now it's become so inbred that its movies are unwatchable. Actors are all alike in the way manikins are. Intellectually they really are, like flatlined, because as Ricky Gervais said they spent less time in school then Greta Thunberg has. Johansson believed she deserved to play in Ghost in a Shell over an Asian actress playing the part of Motoko Kusanagi. I didn’t watch the movie because would never watch her in a movie. But it would like watching a white actress in blackface playing a black character or a white actor playing a Native American character. It’s sickening. Besides, she’s not that attractive, in the way Jennifer Lawrence really isn’t all that attractive. She’s no Emma Stone, Charlize Theron, Jennifer Connelly, or Yifei Liu and Ziyi Zhang. We certainly don’t want to go back to Hollywood’s golden years. That would just be embarrassing, I mean like Grace Kelly, Natalie Wood, Elizabeth Taylor, Ingrid Bergman, Hedy Lamarr and Audrey Hepburn. Like I said, embarrassing. Scarlett has described herself as Jewish. (Wikipedia) In Hollywood that is the best way to go to the front of the casting line—if there is any line at all. She would be perfect to play Abraham's wife Sarah, but not Motoko Kusanagi. In Hollywood inbreeding and money decide who gets a part. That is one reason why I stick with manga and video games, to avoid Hollywood altogether. The other I simply get sick of seeing all those faces over and over again.
